g.text: Client OS
Quickcovert (our web app)
FFmpeg Virtual File System
Flow of Time
1. App prompts opening the OS
file explorer
2. System returns reference to
selected files and gives page
read access to the file's data
3. Select output file name and type in
browser UI. Click Convert
4. Input file is loaded into FFmpeg virtual file system
5. Output file is created based on requested file type and
stored in FFmpeg virtual file system
6. Output file is stored in browser memory
and made accessible through an objectURL
7. (Cleanup) Input and Output file are deleted from FFmpeg
virtual file system. We can still access the Output file stored in
browser memory.
8. File is downloaded onto the host
machine from the objectURL
*We are actually referring to the permissions and storage of our single web app, not the entire web browser
9. objectURL is revoked and the browser
memory is freed
